2026-04-16 07:50:27 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['Control Module 1', 'Control Module 2', 'Control Module 3', 'Control Module 4', 'Control Module 5', 'Control Module 6', 'Control Module 7', 'Control Module 8'] hypothesis_explanation='The absence of all switch indicator (red) LEDs in every control module explains why there is no visible indicator activity, and crucially, since the indicator LEDs are physically removed, the circuit path for current flow through each module is open at that point (because the indicator-resistor chain is not completed, leaving a break in series). Thus, current cannot traverse any control module, so no current reaches the load module and the lamp cannot turn on. Permanently removing all indicator LEDs has interrupted the path.'
